# Architecture context (Monkeyland / Agent Canvas)

This project has a **large spec** in `monkeyland.md` (Tauri, Rust core, 20 agents, PTY pool, browser pool, etc.). To avoid confusion and scope creep:

## Use monkeyland.md for constraints, not as a todo list

- **Do** use it to respect architectural rules (e.g. DOM canvas only, no WebGL; per-session SQLite; PTYs in Rust when that stage is active).
- **Do not** implement stages or features that are not required by the **current task** in `docs/tasks/in-progress/`. If the task is “canvas prompt element,” do not add PTY, browser, or replay — that is out of scope.

## Critical rules (summary)

When your code touches these areas, comply with the spec:

| Area | Rule |
|------|------|
| Canvas | DOM + CSS transforms only. No WebGL, PixiJS, or Canvas 2D for the main canvas. |
| Terminals | PTYs in Rust (portable-pty), not Node. (Relevant when Stage 3 is in scope.) |
| Browser | One Chromium instance; browser context pool. (Relevant when Stage 4 is in scope.) |
| Storage | Per-session SQLite files; no single shared DB. (Relevant when Stage 2+ is in scope.) |
| Agents | Lightweight; JSON-RPC to core; they do not own PTYs or browsers. |

## Entry point

- **Scope** is defined in **monkeyland.md** §7 (Stages 1–6). Agents derive the next task from that section and the **Source** lines in `docs/tasks/done/`; no human is required to pick the next task.
- For “what to do right now,” use **docs/CONTEXT.md** and **docs/tasks/in-progress/*.md**; implement only that task.
